\lsoffBefore there was anything or anyone, in an incomprehensibly
vast silence and darkness... there was Trailia.
This starts as a tale of the Overworld's delicate balance. How it was
created by a group of gods with unique and mystifying powers, united under
one banner by the all-seeing Trailia. These beings were known as the Immortals,
meant to protect the Overworld and cultivate its growth until the end of time.
Unfortunately, as many tales do, this becomes a story of distrust and betrayal.
For oftentimes, the greatest power is vested in those who
would choose to wield it for their own motives.
It attacked. An attack that could not be carried out by pure violence... no, something worse.
The evil god destroyed the very fabric of the Above, renouncing the immortality
of its brethren and sentencing them to an eternity on the mortal plane.
There is something to be said about a fate worse than death itself.
It took the interference of Trailia to stop the evil god's rampage,
sentencing it to the same fate it had brought upon so many. Banished
from the Above and cast down to the Overworld, it was doomed to fall
and perish on the cold hard ground.
This was not without a cost. Even with the death of the body, the evil god's
\c[30]soul\c[0] remained vicious and bitter.  If the Above fell, so would the Overworld...
so Trailia had no choice to cut ties between the two planes, to ensure the \c[30]soul\c[0]
would never be able to return to the Above.
With the Overworld no longer governed by the Immortals, chaos and warfare broke out across
the land. And even though the \c[30]soul\c[0] of the god was allegedly sealed away by a group of mages,
never to be found again... something about the way history repeats itself makes it seem like
the \c[30]soul\c[0] has since been found, \c[30]its\c[0] evil unleashed upon the Overworld once more.
